  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing the Indonesian Request**\n\nI\'m currently dissecting the Indonesian request. It\'s a call for an interactive website in red and white, inspired by a provided visual but needing logical adjustments. My focus is on understanding the specifics of the interactive elements and the intended user experience, considering the indicated flaws. I\'m starting to visualize the scope of the project.\n\n\n**Clarifying Technical Specifications**\n\nI\'m now diving into the technical aspects. After reviewing the Indonesian request, I\'ve translated it and am working to interpret the \"flaws\" mentioned. I\'m focusing on incorporating responsive design and hotlinking images from HTML. I am now exploring the uploaded files and the PDF, which appears to be a project report from \"TIM LOGIXA.\" I am assessing the available technical skills needed for this project.\n\n\n**Evaluating Logical Flow Issues**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the logical flaws in the visual reference. The user specifically flagged issues in the logical flow, so I\'m paying close attention to that area. The request describes a public tracking page with a package tracking number (\"PMI-2024-X8J9\"), along with a \"Detail Kiriman\" (shipment details) and \"Riwayat Perjalanan\" (journey history). I\'ll analyze how these elements interact. I need to determine if an AI is asked.\n\n\n**Reordering Timeline Events**\n\nI\'m now investigating the timeline presented. There\'s a clear chronological inconsistency: \"Diterima di Gudang Transit\" is listed *before* \"Dikemas Ulang.\" I am reviewing the order as either ascending or descending, but there\'s a problem, as repacking \"Dikemas Ulang\" could have happened before arrival \"Diterima di Gudang Transit\". I am also confirming the origin (JKT) and destination (Cianjur) of the shipment, including the transit point in Bandung.\n\n\n**Mapping Out Logistic Systems**\n\nI\'m now integrating information from the \"LHAMS\" system. I see this includes warehouse inventory, scanning procedures for new goods with viability assessments, and repacking categories. There\'s also a process for destroying expired goods and a mobile dispatch component tracking delivery orders, which includes an offline synchronization option. The system seems comprehensive.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will list the files in the directory to explore the workspace structure."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 501271466
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
