  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Skill Relevancy**\n\nI\'ve been going through the available skills to determine which ones are relevant. So far, the focus is on a review, eliminating options like Cloud SQL and Firebase integrations, as they don\'t seem applicable to the current task. I am working on the next skill to test.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Local Storage**\n\nI\'ve decided on local storage as the default approach. The request implicitly suggests this, and it aligns with the application setup. I will prioritize `localStorage` with React state management unless there are specific requirements to implement something different.\nI have also eliminated various APIs, as well as features. I am trying to determine if Gemini is relevant given the wording from the user.\n\n\n**Evaluating Mapping Relevance**\n\nI\'ve dismissed `google-maps-platform` for now, given the lack of mapping keys and the offline-first requirement. A custom SVG or canvas-based map with real-time route path simulation appears more suitable. I\'m keeping `image-generation` in mind for potential illustrations or banners. Other integrations are not relevant. My understanding of the request leads me to think a beautiful, tailored Tailwind UI is the best bet, per the request.\nI am now focused on evaluating the provided layout reference in the user prompt.\n\n\n**Defining UI/UX Elements**\n\nI\'m now identifying the key UI/UX elements from the provided information. This involves determining the necessary components for an \"Anda\" input tracker, shipment details, map placeholders, and a \"Riwayat Perjalanan\" timeline. I am translating these elements into their respective UI components. The goal is to capture the requirements of the dispatch screens, as well.\n\n\n**Designing Unified Navigation**\n\nI\'m now integrating all requested views into a single, unified application. I\'m focusing on a high-fidelity experience by adding a layout switcher or simulation area. This will allow interaction with Public, Admin, and Mobile Dispatch views within a single-screen layout, featuring an interactive navigator. I am working on building out the \"Portal Publik\" functionality, which will enable the user to track shipments. I\'ve also spotted a logic flaw in the provided timeline image, which I will resolve.\n\n\n**Revising Timeline Logic**\n\nI\'ve identified a flaw in the timeline image, specifically with the \"Dikemas Ulang\" and \"Diterima di Gudang Transit\" statuses. I\'m focusing on ensuring chronological accuracy, and I\'m updating my approach, so the list progresses top-to-bottom: Starting from the top, to the ending at the bottom. The most recent status should appear on top, as an active event, and the most recent previous events should appear below, and inactive. The logical flow needs an update.\n\n\n**Correcting Timeline Sequence**\n\nI\'ve determined that the timeline image has an incorrect chronological sequence. The current top-to-bottom flow contradicts the timestamps. I\'m restructuring the events to follow a clear, descending order of progress, with the most recent status appearing at the top, and earlier events descending below. \"Dikemas Ulang\" should come before \"Diterima di Gudang Transit\" in the correct order.\n\n\n**Refining Timeline Structure**\n\nI am now focusing on refining the timeline structure, to ensure clarity and logical order. The structure should reflect the correct order of events for a shipment, with future events shown as \"incoming\". \"Diterima di Gudang Transit\" is now confirmed as an earlier step, and should come before \"Dikemas Ulang\" in the correct sequence. I\'m also incorporating the requirement of the latest entry at the top for an inverse chronological approach. The current task is to review and parse OCR information from a provided PDF report.\n\n\n**Conceptualizing Application Architecture**\n\nI\'m now integrating this comprehensive system report into the design. The goal is a high-fidelity container showcasing all modules: real-time inventory, QR/barcode tracking, procurement digitalization, a field app, public portal traceability, beneficiary database with validation, triage and repacking, expiry warning, and offline-first syncing. I\'m visualizing a red and white theme for a gorgeous and interactive website, highlighting each module distinctly, and demonstrating those screens!\n\n\n**Visualizing Module Integration**\n\nI am now focusing on integrating the three distinct environments requested into a unified experience, specifically, the Public Tracking Portal, Admin Web Portal, and Mobile Dispatch App. I\'m imagining interactive containers to showcase the modules, with clear navigation between the Public Portal for shipment tracking (correct timeline included), the Admin Portal with inventory, beneficiary verification, and reporting, and the Mobile Dispatch App (simulator) for volunteers. My task is now to conceptualize the integration of these modules within the unified website framework.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will view the `/src/index.css` file to see how styles and fonts are structured."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 22
      nanos: 78850053
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
