  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Admin Panel Structure**\n\nI\'m now focusing on outlining the structure for the `src/components/AdminPortal.tsx` component. The initial plan involves an inventory tab as the default and a sidebar. The sidebar will include a dashboard with summary stats like total items and alerts for expired or pending items.\n\n\n**Detailing Inventory Features**\n\nI\'m currently fleshing out the inventory section. The core is a table showcasing items with QR code thumbnails, stock levels, locations, and status badges. I\'m building out filtering options based on warehouse region and categories. I\'ve designed a \"Tambah Barang\" button which triggers a modal. This modal guides the user through scanning a barcode, assigning a quality status, and selecting a repacking category, leading to the item being saved. I\'m adding an \"expired < 30 days\" action.\n\n\n**Designing Disposal Processes**\n\nI\'m now detailing the \"Prosedur Pemusnahan Barang\" modal, triggered after item inspection. I\'ve defined information fields for item name, quantity, and expiration date. There\'s a text area for disposal reasons and an upload section for authorization documents. Users can either cancel or \"Sahkan Pemusnahan Digital,\" which marks the item as disposed of.\n\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/components/AdminPortal.tsx` component. It will house the enterprise administration dashboard, featuring multi-warehouse management, active status triage repacking modals, chemical/medical disposal modals, duplicate identification tools, and EVA/IFRC-compliant reporting blocks."
