  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Mobile Dispatch**\n\nI\'m now focusing on designing the mobile dispatch simulator component, specifically `/src/components/MobileDispatch.tsx`. Initial thoughts revolve around implementing a realistic physical phone layout, for better user understanding.\n\n\n**Developing Offline Functionality**\n\nI\'m now integrating offline mode, adding a toggle switch between \"Online\" and \"Offline\" states. When offline, I\'ll display warning banners like \"Mode Luring Aktif\" or \"Koneksi terputus. Data aman di memori lokal.\" I\'m also designing the login screen (optional) and the home screen with bento cards for order indicators and task lists that reflect the offline state. Clicking on a DO will trigger the \"Distribusi Bantuan\" form.\n\n\n**Implementing QR Scanning**\n\nI\'m now implementing the QR scanning button, \"Pindai QR Paket Bantuan\", with form fields for identity, recipient details, and digital signature capture. The \"Ambil Foto Wajah / Bukti\" button will simulate image capture using an avatar for demonstration, while the signature pad will be a highlight using a Canvas element. Local data saving will validate input and add entries to the sync queue.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/components/MobileDispatch.tsx` component. It includes a beautiful smartphone browser simulator framing the \"LHAMS Field Dispatch\" mobile system. It features interactive signature pad canvases, dynamic image capture simulation, real-time local state tracking, battery/connectivity simulator toggles, and sync queues pushing local data directly into the Central Verification system."
